abraham lincoln is an 11-foot (3.4 m) bronze statue of the sixteenth president in lytle park within downtown cincinnati, ohio, united states. the charles p. taft family commissioned artist george grey barnard to complete a statue in commemoration of the centenary of the lincoln's birth. the sculpture was unveiled at lytle park on march 31, 1917. former u.s. president william howard taft, the younger brother of charles, delivered the dedication speech.